  "name": "allow-non-admin-community-20260324-1436",
  "idea": "Allow non-admin community members to message the BNDC Discord bot directly, with access controls. Key requirements: 1) Add a flag on the members table (e.g. can_message_bot) that controls who can interact with the bot. 2) Cordon off sensitive operations so non-admin users can only do safe read-only things (search messages, look up member info, etc.) while admins retain full control (delete messages, send messages, manage server, etc.). 3) Figure out what data/operations are actually sensitive and should be restricted. The bot currently only works via admin_chat - need to understand the full current architecture and design how to open it up safely.",
